Title: Being A Scouter
Description:
HYBRID COURSE

PLEASE READ BEFORE BOOKING:

This course covers the What, Why and How of Scouting and is compulsory for any adult who wishes to volunteer with young people in a Scout Group.  You must have previously completed the induction with your Group Leader and have up-to-date vetting before you can attend this course.  This is a hybrid course and you must attend all three blocks.

Down & Connor Part 1 – will take place ONLINE VIA ZOOM on 27th September 19:30 – 21:30. Part 2 -the full-day in person Scout Training will take place in Carryduff Scout Den on 30th September 09:30 – 17:00.  Part 3 - 3rd October Online 19:00-22:00.

Erne Part 1 – will take place ONLINE VIA ZOOM on 27th September 19:30 – 21:30. Part 2 the full-day in person Scout Training will take place in xxxx  Scout Den on 1st October 09:30 – 17:00 Part 3 5th October Online 19:00-22:00

Brian Boru Part 1 - will take place ONLINE VIA ZOOM on 27th September 19:30 – 21:30. Part 2 the full-day in person Scout Training will take place in Cookstown Scout Den on 7th October 09:30 – 17:00 Part 3 - 10th October Online 19:00-22:00

Errigal Part 1 - will take place ONLINE VIA ZOOM on 27th September 19:30 – 21:30. Part 2 the full-day in person Scout Training will take place in Carndonagh Scout Den on 8th October 09:30 – 17:00.  Part 3 12th October Online 19:00-22:00.
Participants must ensure they are able to attend all modules before booking the course.  Your zoom link for attending Part 1 and Part 3 will be sent 48 hours before the course start time.

Lunch will be provided on part 2.

Being a Scouter is one course delivered across three blocks.  It is vital to attend all three blocks in full.  Due to the technical challenges and the burden on volunteers, it is not possible to complete blocks at your leisure – all three must be completed as specified above.  Thank you for your understanding with this.
